  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your<strong> kidney beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1591198466016-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1591198466016-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1591198466016-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1591198466016-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1591198466016-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and cook for 30 secs further</p><p>Add the<strong> drained kidney beans</strong> with 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [125ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until the beans are beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1591198470899-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1591198470899-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1591198470899-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1591198470899-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1591198470899-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim and finely slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> and add to a large mixing bowl</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong> and add it to the bowl</p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong> into the bowl, season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix thoroughly – this is your<strong> cheesy sweetcorn mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
